Issue description Following a force shutdown of the server, the system failed to boot with following message:
initramfs: waiting for /dev/mapper/ubuntu&ndash;vg-ubuntu&ndash;lv to appear &hellip;
timeout waiting &hellip;
&hellip;
Then the init process crashed with kernel panic.
Solution As if it&rsquo;s due to initramfs damage by the improper shutdown, so the solution is to re-generate the initramfs.
Boot from a live CD/USB Could either burn a live iso to a USB stick or mount the ISO to the server (how to mount the ISO to a server via its BMC/IPMI tools, is out of the scope).
